comment: This app, being free, does a good job of caching and storing a wide selection of maps for use offline.  It only falls short as it still seems a bit "rough" around the edges; the interface isn't all that intuitive and unless you're in an airplane, I'm not sure how useful the scale rings are (i.e. in the mountains).  I haven't had any significant performance issues on the Samsung Galaxy Rugby Pro, with the exception of some sluggish map loading when online and a bit of intermittent temperament when downloading for offline use.  Overall, this app answers the call for offline map use and has more than enough feature to find your way out of the wilderness in an emergency.

title: Great app, responsive developer.
comment: The app its self is the best for my mapping needs that I've found. It's clean, quick, stable and has all the features I value. I rely on having offline mapping databases on my SD card for when I'm hiking, out of data signal, travelling abroad, to save the battery a little and finally recycling old phones as offfline GPS units for family. All on a free / donation basis :-) I finally got round to buying the donation version after the developer responded to a bug I encountered, complete with a fixed build of the program the next day! Very few commercial developers will give you anything close to that level of support. Thanks to the dev for this great app and my highest recommendations to anyone considering installing or supporting it by donating.  Some features I hope get added in the future: Ability to download non-rectangular regions of maps. Ability to remove regions from existing map databases. Search feature in POI list. Share tracks, POIs and maybe even small regions of map tile via bluetooth with other peoples phones running rmaps.
